    thinking: "**Prioritizing Security and Design**\n\nI\'ve decided to prioritize both security and visual appeal. I\'ll be implementing `no-referrer` for enhanced privacy. I\'m also thinking of using high-quality visual placeholders or, if preferred, generating images. Furthermore, I\'m leaning toward designing custom elements with responsive Tailwind UI sections for optimal flexibility.\n\n\n**Refining Core Structure**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the codebase organization. I\'m planning out the file structure meticulously, envisioning a `/src` directory with specific type definitions, such as `/src/types.ts` for all data models. I also have component files planned, including `/src/components/Header.tsx`, `/src/components/Hero.tsx`, `/src/components/KenapaWebsite.tsx`, `/src/components/Layanan.tsx`, and a show-stopping `/src/components/PricingCalculator.tsx`. The goal is to build out a structured, scalable system.\n\n\n**Envisioning Feature Implementation**\n\nI\'m now integrating the pricing calculator with a real-time \"mockup preview\" and WhatsApp integration. I\'m also planning the `/src/components/Portfolio.tsx` section as a grid featuring interactive demos. A carousel for testimonials will be implemented via `/src/components/Testimonials.tsx`. Then, I\'ll build accordions within `/src/components/FAQ.tsx`. The site\'s footer will be in `/src/components/Footer.tsx`. Finally, `/src/App.tsx` will coordinate everything, and contain any consultation callbacks.\nI\'m also considering the design, making it modern and elegant with a white and light-gray color scheme.\n\n\n**Defining Visual Accents**\n\nI\'m now thinking about the color palette, and leaning towards an elegant design with emerald-green accents. This aligns well with trust and growth, and subtly complements the WhatsApp CTAs. I\'m also preparing to develop the `/src/types.ts` file first, followed by the calculator details. I need to make a UI to allow the user to select business categories, the various features listed, and the number of pages.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the `/src/types.ts` file. This file will declare the structured data models, package options, and customizable feature lists for our interactive website quote calculator and portfolio gallery."
